Betty Harte https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Betty_Harte 0 Betty Harte (May 13, 1882 – January 3, 1965) was an American actress of the silent era. Born Daisy Mae Light, she appeared in 108 films between 1908 and 1916 after starting out as a secretary for a newspaper. She was born in Lebanon, Pennsylvania and died in Sunland, California.
